    "body": "<!-- Explain, in a clear and concise way, the command you ran and the result you were trying to achieve.\r\nExample: \"I ran `spack find` to list all the installed packages and ...\" -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[The `cudnn` spec](https://github.com/spack/spack/blob/develop/var/spack/repos/builtin/packages/cudnn/package.py\r\n) should be updated to add version `8.2.2` wich supports Cuda 11.4. This is an issue because 11.4 is now the default cuda version. See the [cudnn support mattrix](https://docs.nvidia.com/deeplearning/cudnn/support-matrix/index.html).\r\n\r\nI had some conflicts trying to install `py-cupy` due to that.\r\nThanks for the support\r\n\r\n@adamjstewart  @bvanessen",
